qas.question: What was Tennessee's most common self-reported ethnic group in 2000?
What percent of Tennessee residents self-reported their ethnic group as Irish in 2000?
Which European ancestries are most common among self-identified ethnic "Americans" in Tennessee?
What European national ancestry was claimed by 45% of Tennessee residents in 1980?

context: In 2000, the five most common self-reported ethnic groups in the state were: <a0_0>American<a0_0/> (17.3%), African American (13.0%), Irish (<a1_0>9.3%<a1_0/>), English (9.1%), and German (8.3%). Most Tennesseans who self-identify as having American ancestry are of <a2_0>English and Scotch-Irish<a2_0/> ancestry. An estimated 21–24% of Tennesseans are of predominantly English ancestry.
